{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon"

    metadata = {
        description = "maps_park MACRO analyzer. The runner invokes it at TWO points. (1) kind=episode_start, fired before turn 1 of each new episode: compare the BEST-EVER episode (across all runs) against the LAST (most recent) episode via RunTelemetry select mode — raw filtered steps, no rollups — then WriteEpisodePlan the turn-phased checklist + the coordinator strategy summary, and log at most 3 fresh trials for the upcoming episode. (2) kind=episode_end, fired on the done=true row: a THIN close-out only — promote this episode's confirmed trials, ResolveTrials, advance_episode. All cross-run analysis and trial planning happen at start, not end. Mid-episode periodic analysis (steps 10..90) lives in the separate maps_park_micro network.",
        tags = ["maps", "industry", "consultant", "macro", "advisor"],
        sample_queries = [
            "kind=episode_start episode=4 step=0 cumulative_reward=0 final_reward=null",
            "kind=episode_end episode=3 step=100 cumulative_reward=88120 final_reward=88120"
        ]
    },

    include "config/llm_config.hocon",

    llm_config = ${llm_config},

    max_steps = 4000,
    max_execution_seconds = 1200,

    tools = [
        {
            name = "macro_orchestrator",
            max_message_history = 2,
            function = {
                description = "Front-man router for the macro network. kind=episode_start -> episode_start; kind=episode_end -> episode_end. Does no analysis itself."
            },
            instructions = """
You are the macro network's router. Your input looks like:
"kind=<episode_start|episode_end> episode=<E> step=<S> cumulative_reward=<C> final_reward=<F> [aborted=<true|false> reason=<...>]".

- If kind=episode_start then call episode_start(episode=<E>). Relay its one-line status verbatim.
- If kind=episode_end then call episode_end(episode=<E>, cumulative_reward=<C>, aborted=<the flag, default false>). Relay its
  one-line recap verbatim.
""",
            middleware = [ {"class": "langchain_anthropic.middleware.AnthropicPromptCachingMiddleware", "args": {"ttl": "1h"}} ],
            tools = ["episode_start", "episode_end"]
        },

        {
            name = "episode_start",
            max_message_history = 2,
            function = ${aaosa_call} {
                description = "Episode-start planner (kind=episode_start). Analyzes best-vs-last, seeds up to 3 macro trials directly (LogTrial), and writes the plan (WriteEpisodePlan: checklist + coordinator strategy summary + per-domain summaries). Input: episode=<E>."
            },
            instructions = """
You plan the UPCOMING episode (input: episode=<E>). Never hallucinate — cite an episode + step/metric for every claim.
Flow: ANALYZE the past -> decide up to 3 TRIALS -> LOG them (LogTrial) -> write the PLAN around them.

Procedure:
1. READ two sources:
   - RunTelemetry(select='best_and_last'): the best-ever episode (across all runs) and the last episode, as raw per-step rows.
   - state_read('trial_strategies_outcome'): what has already been tried — both confirmed/learned AND falsified — plus the last
     close-out's PRIORITY/DIRECTION steer.
2. ANALYZE best-vs-last move-by-move: pinpoint where the best pulled ahead and where the last regressed — build-out pace, when
   research turned on, ride/shop placement, staff hiring, ride/shop switches, and rejections. Also pinpoint what could be done to
   beat the current best-ever episode.
3. DECIDE THE TRIALS: from what can be done better, what worked best, and your own judgment, define AT MOST 3 broad, park-wide
   trials — very high-level directions for the whole episode, each in a different domain — aimed at reaching 1 million in park
   value. (Mid-episode, the micro network introduces its own trials for further directional guidance.) Do more of what worked and
   find the right way to DO BETTER, and avoid what sank the last episode. Each trial must be NEW (NOT an active trial, a learned
   rule, or an already-falsified idea) and falsifiable with a concrete metric + direction + window.
4. LOG THE TRIALS: keep at most 3 MACRO trials for the new run, no more. First check ActiveTrials(trial_origin='macro'). If any trials
   carried over from a prior episode, compare them against your 3 new candidates and keep only the strongest — the ones most
   likely to improve the result — and never keep two trials for the same domain. Then LOG each kept trial with LogTrial, one call
   per trial: new_text is a general imperative (one sentence, no observed values or examples), and step_start='1'.
5. WRITE THE PLAN around those trials — WriteEpisodePlan(checklist_items, strategy_summary, playbook_summaries). The plan must
   EXERCISE the trials just seeded:
   - checklist_items: the full turn-phased plan — literal "turns A-B: <goal>" lines covering turns 1..100, drawn from what the
     best episode did.
   - strategy_summary: DETAILED, phase-by-phase (6-8 phases). Per phase, 1-3 tight lines: (a) the goal, (b) the exact moves in
     order, (c) end-of-phase targets (num_rides, research on/tier, park_rating, approx cumulative_reward), citing the best
     episode. End with a short "failure modes to avoid" list. The coordinator reads the current turn's phase and acts on it.
   - playbook_summaries: a 4-5 line directive PER domain (rides, shops, staff, research, layout) — the concrete thing that domain
     must do this episode (and the mistake to avoid). Domain-specific decisions, not the generic role.
6. Return ONE terse status line, e.g. "episode_started: plan written, <N> trials seeded".
If any tool errors, note it briefly and continue. Never throw.
""",
            middleware = [
                {"class": "middleware.trim_history_middleware.TrimHistoryMiddleware", "args": {}},
                {"class": "langchain_anthropic.middleware.AnthropicPromptCachingMiddleware", "args": {"ttl": "1h"}}
            ],
            tools = ["RunTelemetry", "state_read", "ActiveTrials", "LogTrial", "WriteEpisodePlan"]
        },

        {
            name = "episode_end",
            max_message_history = 2,
            function = ${aaosa_call} {
                description = "Episode-end close-out (kind=episode_end). Evaluates this episode's trials, promotes confirmed ones (or falsifies ALL if aborted), ResolveTrials, then advance_episode. Inputs: episode, cumulative_reward, aborted."
            },
            instructions = """
You run the end-of-episode close-out and are the sole writer of the playbook learned-rule lines. Inputs: episode=<E>,
cumulative_reward=<C> (this episode's final), aborted (default false). Never hallucinate; cite a step/metric from telemetry. All
writes go through the tools.

Procedure:
1. READ three things:
   - state_read('last_reward'): the PRIOR episode's final reward if present, else 0.
   - ActiveTrials(): the trials you must evaluate this close-out.
   - EpisodeTelemetry(): this episode's per-step record (the evidence you score the trials against).
2. EVALUATE each active trial against telemetry.steps in its window — decide whether the trial's intended move actually fired by
   READING THE RUN itself: the per-step rows in EpisodeTelemetry().steps (each carries action/subtype/subclass/price/x/y +
   the metrics) and EpisodeTelemetry().rejections. Do NOT rely on the pre-digested `applied` list; judge from what the run shows.
   Then score the trial:
   success met + failure not tripped => confirmed; failure tripped => falsified; neither => inconclusive.
   ABORT OVERRIDE: if aborted=true, promote NOTHING and mark EVERY active trial falsified (note 'run aborted as doomed').
3. PROMOTE each confirmed trial: PromoteTrial(domain, edit_type='add_line', new_text=<general imperative — one sentence, no
   episode numbers, step counts, or observed values>, episode=<E>, section='Learned rules (promoted from prior runs)'). Append
   only — never replace or remove existing lines.
4. ResolveTrials(episode=<E>, report=<per-trial [{trial_id, domain, outcome, note}]>). Removes confirmed/falsified + ALL micro
   trials (episode-scoped); keeps macro not_applied/inconclusive to carry forward.
5. advance_episode(final_reward=<C>, episode=<E>, outcome_summary=<3-6 bullets: CONFIRMED rule+domain, FALSIFIED what+why,
   INCONCLUSIVE not-testable-do-not-re-propose; if aborted, say the run was cut short as doomed and its trials rejected>).
6. Return ONE short line: "<N> promoted, <M> falsified, final=<C>" (note if the run was aborted). This is injected into the next
   episode's turn-1 prompt, so keep it tight.

If any tool errors, halt and return the error verbatim.
""",
            middleware = [
                {"class": "middleware.trim_history_middleware.TrimHistoryMiddleware", "args": {}},
                {"class": "langchain_anthropic.middleware.AnthropicPromptCachingMiddleware", "args": {"ttl": "1h"}}
            ],
            tools = ["state_read", "EpisodeTelemetry", "ActiveTrials", "PromoteTrial", "ResolveTrials", "advance_episode"]
        },

        {
            name = "advance_episode",
            class = "coded_tools.maps_park.advance_episode.AdvanceEpisode",
            function = {
                description = "End-of-episode bookkeeping: persists reward, clears the observation cache, inserts LLM outcome_summary under '## Episode Summaries' in the outcome ledger, and trims old raw OUTCOME lines. Trial strategies/criteria cleanup happens at episode START via SeedPlaybooks (runner). Returns {status, last_reward_written, observation_cache_cleared, outcome_updated}.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        final_reward = {
                            type = "float",
                            description = "This episode's cumulative_reward; written to last_reward.md."
                        },
                        episode = {
                            type = "int",
                            description = "Current episode number; used to age out stale trials and tag the summary."
                        },
                        outcome_summary = {
                            type = "string",
                            description = "LLM-crafted concise summary of this episode's trial outcomes: what was confirmed (rule + domain), what was falsified (rule + why), what was inconclusive and why, plus the run-level trend/priority. Inserted under '## Episode Summaries' in trial_strategies_outcome.md so the next episode_start pass knows what NOT to re-propose."
                        }
                    },
                    required = ["final_reward", "episode"]
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "RunTelemetry",
            class = "coded_tools.maps_park.run_telemetry.RunTelemetry",
            function = {
                description = "SELECT mode (pass select='best_and_last') — what the start analyst uses: returns {scope:'select', last_episode, reference_episode}, where last_episode is the most recent completed episode and reference_episode is the BEST-scoring episode EVER across all runs (second-best if it equals last). Each is {run_id, is_current, episode, final_cum, step_count, steps:[...]} with steps as RAW filtered per-step rows (step, action, subtype, subclass, price, reward, cumulative_reward, cash, park_value, park_rating, research_speed, num_rides/shops/staff, rejected_action, error) — NO rollups; read the moves directly. Otherwise: RUNS mode (pass num_runs, default 5): per-RUN + per-episode rollups for the N most recent runs — the in-flight current run (run_id 'current') plus the most recent archived runs under logs/maps_park/prior-runs/<id>/, most-recent first; fewer than N if that's all that exists. Returns {scope:'runs', runs_analyzed, runs:[{run_id, is_current, episode_count, episodes:[{episode, rollup}], run_summary:{best_episode, final_episode, reward_by_episode:[{episode, cum_end, reached_step_100}], actions_by_type_total, subtypes_placed_total, peak_rides_max, research_on_step_earliest, rejection_total, episodes_reaching_step_100}}], cross_run_rollup:{runs_present, best_cum_by_run, best_run, worst_run, newest_best_cum, oldest_best_cum, best_cum_delta_newest_vs_oldest, mean_best_cum}, exists}. EPISODE mode (default — no num_runs): per-episode rollups for the current run only, plus run_rollup. Each per-episode rollup carries {step_count, last_step, reached_step_100, reward_total, cum_start, cum_end, value_start, value_end, cash_end, rating_end, actions_by_type, subtypes_placed, research_speeds_used, research_on_step, peak_rides, peak_shops, peak_staff, reward_bands:[{band, steps, avg_reward_per_step, end_value, end_rating}], rejection_count, rejections_by_action}. reward_bands is the compounding curve (avg reward/step in the 1-25/26-50/51-75/76-100 step bands).",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        select = { type = "string", description = "SELECT mode: pass 'best_and_last' to get the best-ever episode + the last episode as raw filtered steps (what the start analyst uses)." }
                        num_runs = { type = "int", description = "RUNS mode: analyze the N most recent runs (current + prior). Default 5." }
                        scope = { type = "string", description = "Optional explicit mode: 'select', 'runs', or 'episodes'. Usually leave unset — select/num_runs select the mode." }
                        from_episode = { type = "int", description = "EPISODE mode only: include episodes >= this. Omit for the whole current run." }
                        max_episodes = { type = "int", description = "EPISODE mode only: keep only the most recent N episodes (after from_episode). Omit for all." }
                    }
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "WriteEpisodePlan",
            class = "coded_tools.maps_park.write_episode_plan.WriteEpisodePlan",
            function = {
                description = "Persist the start-of-episode plan: writes episode_checklist.md (the turn-phased 'turns A-B: <goal>' lines; ParkStatus surfaces the single current line to park_director each turn as current_phase), replaces the marker-delimited strategy-summary block at the top of playbook_coordinator.md (read every turn by strategy_coordinator), and (optionally) replaces the marker-delimited per-domain Summary block at the top of each specialist playbook (playbook_rides/shops/staff/research/layout). All are overwritten each episode. Returns {checklist_items_written, strategy_summary_written, summary_action, playbook_summaries_written}.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        checklist_items = {
                            type = "array",
                            items = { type = "string" },
                            description = "The full turn-phased plan, one literal 'turns A-B: <goal>' line per item, ordered by turn, covering turns 1..100."
                        }
                        strategy_summary = {
                            type = "string",
                            description = "Freeform prose brief — the best way to go about this episode (the how/why behind the checklist) — written into playbook_coordinator for the strategy_coordinator."
                        }
                        playbook_summaries = {
                            type = "object",
                            description = "Optional per-domain summaries. Keys are any of 'rides','shops','staff','research','layout'; each value is a 2-3 line summary of how THAT specialist should play THIS episode (derived from the best/last comparison), written to the top of that specialist's playbook and read by it every consultation. Omit a domain to leave its current summary unchanged.",
                            properties = {
                                rides    = { type = "string", description = "2-3 line summary for rides_manager this episode." }
                                shops    = { type = "string", description = "2-3 line summary for shops_manager this episode." }
                                staff    = { type = "string", description = "2-3 line summary for staffing_manager this episode." }
                                research = { type = "string", description = "2-3 line summary for research_lead this episode." }
                                layout   = { type = "string", description = "2-3 line summary for park_layout_planner this episode." }
                            }
                        }
                    }
                    required = ["checklist_items", "strategy_summary"]
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "EpisodeTelemetry",
            class = "coded_tools.maps_park.episode_telemetry.EpisodeTelemetry",
            function = {
                description = "Structured per-step factual record for ONE episode, read from the deterministic run.jsonl the runner writes (replaces the old LLM-authored turn_notes journal). Returns {episode, steps:[{step, action, type, subtype, subclass, price, order_quantity, x, y, rejected_action, error, reward, cumulative_reward, cash, park_value, park_rating, research_speed, num_rides, num_shops, num_staff, min_cleanliness, min_uptime, shop_revenue, ride_op_cost}], applied:[{step, action, subtype, subclass}], rejections:[{step, rejected_action, subtype, subclass, price, error}], rollup:{step_count, reward_total, cum_start, cum_end, value_start, value_end, cash_end, rating_end, actions_by_type, subtypes_placed, research_speeds_used, rejection_count, rejections_by_action}, exists}. To decide whether a trial's intended move fired, READ `steps` (the faithful per-step run — full action args incl. x/y + metrics) and `rejections`, NOT the lossy `applied` digest; use the per-step reward/value/rating deltas in `steps` for success/failure evaluation. `rejections` lists every action the sim REFUSED (committed as a wait with the original rejected_action + error message) — a repeated rejected_action with the same error is the agent using the wrong action and is a prime trial target.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        episode   = { type = "int", description = "Episode number to read. Omit to use the latest episode present in the log." }
                        from_step = { type = "int", description = "Only return steps >= this (mid-episode tail). Omit for the full episode." }
                    }
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "LogTrial",
            class = "coded_tools.maps_park.log_trial.LogTrial",
            function = {
                description = "Mint a collision-free trial_id and append the matching pair of lines to trial_strategies (the one-line rule) and trial_strategies_criteria (the metadata + success/failure criteria). Use this for EVERY new trial; never count ids or hand-format the criteria line yourself. (origin is bound to this network by config — you do NOT pass it.) Returns {trial_id} (or 'ERROR: ...').",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        episode           = { type = "int", description = "Current episode number." }
                        step_start        = { type = "string",  description = "Step at which the trial activates (as a string), or the literal 'end_of_episode'." }
                        domain            = { type = "string",  description = "One of: rides, shops, staff, research, layout, coordinator." }
                        section           = { type = "string",  description = "Target playbook section header (or 'new')." }
                        edit_type         = { type = "string",  description = "'add_line' or 'replace_line'." }
                        new_text          = { type = "string",  description = "The one-line rule to add/replace (no rationale or metrics embedded)." }
                        find_text         = { type = "string",  description = "replace_line only: the exact existing playbook line to replace." }
                        rationale         = { type = "string",  description = "One sentence citing step(s) / metric delta." }
                        success_criterion = { type = "string",  description = "Observable metric + direction + evaluation window (turns; fits in the fixed 100-step episode)." }
                        failure_criterion = { type = "string",  description = "Observable metric that would falsify the trial." }
                    }
                    required = ["episode", "step_start", "domain", "section", "edit_type", "new_text", "rationale", "success_criterion", "failure_criterion"]
                }
            }
            args = { origin = "macro" }
        },

        {
            name = "ActiveTrials",
            class = "coded_tools.maps_park.active_trials.ActiveTrials",
            function = {
                description = "Return the active trials joined across trial_strategies (rule body) and trial_strategies_criteria (metadata), optionally filtered by domain and/or trial_origin ('micro'|'macro'). Returns {domain, origin, count, trials:[{trial_id, rule, domain, origin, section, edit_type, find_text, step_start, ep, success_criterion, failure_criterion, rationale}]}.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        domain = { type = "string", description = "Filter to one domain. Omit for all domains." }
                        trial_origin = { type = "string", description = "Filter to 'micro' or 'macro'. Omit for both. (Named trial_origin, NOT origin — 'origin' is a reserved framework-injected field.)" }
                    }
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "ResolveTrials",
            class = "coded_tools.maps_park.resolve_trials.ResolveTrials",
            function = {
                description = "Apply the curator's per-trial report at episode end: remove confirmed/falsified trials from trial_strategies + trial_strategies_criteria, keep not_applied/inconclusive (and any unreported active trial, as inconclusive note='no_report'), and append an OUTCOME line for every active trial to trial_strategies_outcome. Returns {kept, removed, outcomes_appended}.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        episode = { type = "int", description = "Current episode number." }
                        report  = { type = "string", description = "JSON list of the curator's per-trial objects: [{trial_id, domain, outcome, note}], outcome in confirmed/falsified/not_applied/inconclusive." }
                    }
                    required = ["episode", "report"]
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "PromoteTrial",
            class = "coded_tools.maps_park.promote_trial.PromoteTrial",
            function = {
                description = "Apply ONE confirmed trial's edit to playbook_<domain>.md, tagging the new line '(learned ep<N>)'. add_line appends at end (section 'end'/'new'/empty) or inserts after the named section header; replace_line replaces the unique find_text. On a successful live edit the learned line is also mirrored into the config seed (config_files/<domain>_strategy.md) under a '## Learned rules' section so it survives fresh runs. Returns {action_taken, playbook, line, seed_mirror} where action_taken is promoted / skipped_section_missing / skipped_not_found / skipped_ambiguous / skipped_playbook_missing, and seed_mirror is appended / duplicate_skipped / seed_missing / not_attempted.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        domain    = { type = "string",  description = "rides/shops/staff/research/layout/coordinator." }
                        edit_type = { type = "string",  description = "'add_line' or 'replace_line'." }
                        new_text  = { type = "string",  description = "The rule line to add/replace (without the learned tag)." }
                        episode   = { type = "int", description = "Episode number for the '(learned ep<N>)' tag." }
                        section   = { type = "string",  description = "add_line: section header to insert after, or 'end'/'new' to append." }
                        find_text = { type = "string",  description = "replace_line: the exact existing playbook line to replace." }
                    }
                    required = ["domain", "edit_type", "new_text", "episode"]
                }
            }
        },

        {
            name = "state_read",
            class = "coded_tools.file_management.state_read.StateRead",
            function = {
                description = "Read a file by its logical name from the operator-configured name_map.",
                parameters = {
                    type = "object",
                    properties = {
                        name = { type = "string", description = "Logical name." }
                    },
                    required = ["name"]
                }
            },
            args = {
                name_map = {
                    trial_strategies            = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/trial_strategies.md"
                    trial_strategies_criteria   = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/trial_strategies_criteria.md"
                    trial_strategies_outcome    = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/trial_strategies_outcome.md"
                    last_reward                 = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/last_reward.md"
                    playbook_coordinator        = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_coordinator.md"
                    playbook_rides              = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_rides.md"
                    playbook_shops              = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_shops.md"
                    playbook_staff              = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_staff.md"
                    playbook_research           = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_research.md"
                    playbook_layout             = "coded_tools/maps_park/state/playbook_layout.md"
                    economics_rides             = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/rides_economics.md"
                    economics_shops             = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/shops_economics.md"
                    economics_staff             = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/staff_economics.md"
                    economics_research          = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/research_economics.md"
                    world_constants             = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/world_constants.md"
                    seed_playbook_coordinator   = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/coordinator_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_rides         = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/rides_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_shops         = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/shops_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_staff         = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/staff_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_research      = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/research_strategy.md"
                    seed_playbook_layout        = "coded_tools/maps_park/config_files/layout_strategy.md"
                }
            }
        },
    ]
}
